Student body Sasco is raising several concerns in higher learning institutions. These include student funding and mandatory vaccinations Sasco's President Bamanye Matiwane speaks more about this. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - The South African Students Congress (Sasco) is threatening to protest at institutions of higher learning. It's demanding an end to mandatory vaccinations and financial exclusions. Sasco says it's open to further engagements with government and higher learning institutions, but it won't hesitate to call a strike if its demands aren't met. Watch the video above for more details.